&lt;img src=&quot;res/sk_blafp/common/rightarrow.gif&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt; Description :&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/font&gt; OBIEE server can allow a specific user to Act As a different user without having to know his credentials. The permissionning is enforced by the configuration. Once Acting as a different user, all the variables and filtering rules associated to the roles of the target user are applied to the source user.[br/]
To see this example, login as Prodney/Admin123, then visit this dashboard. Once here, click on the drop down on top right of the page below the name Prodney, select Act As feature. In the dialog box select a name for a target user : for example Gkendal. Click ok, and navigate back to the same dashboard, see that GKendal security rules now apply.[br/] To return back acting as Prodney, simply click the same path and select Stop Acting As</sawd:HTML>
      </sawd:htmlView>
      
      
